                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14971450" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2015 17:46:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is is possible this is caused by a network issue between the machine where the app runs and remote log archive machine?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14971468" author="hdpham" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2015 17:55:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am doubtful. When we switch out only the Log4j&apos;s jars from 2.4/2.4.1 to 2.3 from our application on the same Linux host everything work.  With 2.4/2.4.1 the archiving file does get created in the remote location but it can&apos;t be written into (always stay at size 0), the running logging file keep increasing well pass the set size limit (e.g. set by SizeBasedTriggeringPolicy).&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15008215" author="tapanirundgren" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 07:44:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I get this same error with RollingRandomAccessFile appender and the size has passed the limit.&lt;br/&gt;
My env. is Java8/Jboss EAP6.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15008327" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 09:10:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you specify your OS name and version, java vendor and version and your log4j2 configuration so we can try to reproduce the issue? Does this always happen or only sometimes?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15008379" author="tapanirundgren" created="Tue, 17 Nov 2015 09:40:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, I am running on Windows 8.1 Oracle JDK 1.8.0_66&lt;br/&gt;
But I found out just few minutes ago that this could be related to configuration file error I had.&lt;br/&gt;
After fixing config error (logger def. with missing appenderRef), the problem went away!&lt;br/&gt;
Added attachment (picture from filesystem)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15030788" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Sun, 29 Nov 2015 03:54:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in master in commit 220d6b8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
